comment: LHH shows that Anthony (NYK) and George (IND) briefly engage and separate while attempting to establish post position.
Ellis (IND) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
LATR and L-Slash show Mahinmi (IND) reaches in and makes contact with the ball. Anthony (NYK) raises his arm as he loses control of the ball.
Turner (IND) sets the screen on Thomas (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

After communicating with the Replay Center using the Player Altercation Trigger, the officials determined that the contact by Anthony warranted a Technical Foul. All Technical Fouls are reviewed by the League Office.
George (IND) sets the screen on Anthony (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] George (IND) jumps to pass and lands prior to releasing the ball.
Porzingis (NYK) disengages from Mahinmi (IND), and steps into Hill's (IND) path without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Hill (IND) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Porzingis (NYK) that does not affect his layup attempt.
Anthony (NYK) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Calderon (NYK) is in a legal rebounding position and does not dislodge Hill (IND).
Mahinmi (IND) and Porzingis (NYK) briefly engage and separate during the inbounds play.
Porzingis (NYK) sets the screen on Ellis (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (IND) legally contests Porzingis' (NYK) jump shot attempt. Any contact to the hand after the release is considered incidental.
Galloway (NYK) commits a take foul on Turner (IND).
George (IND) and Anthony (NYK) briefly engage and separate during the inbounds play.
